    "body": "FWIW, in Sage we can define a specific output region with a context manager.  Anything executed inside the context manager gets some metadata appended to the output messages redirecting the output to a specific place (we do this by appending default metadata to the session python object).  Then when you issue something like a clear_output, it only clears the output pointed to by the metadata.\n\nSo something like:\n\n``` python\nwith new_output_region() as f:\n    some code that outputs things\n    will be put in a div tied to f\nsome other stuff\nf.clear_output() # clears the div f\n```\n"
  },
