    "body": "I don't think we have a leaky abstraction with separate widget and output areas in the same input cell. Here are the abstractions:\n1. All widgets go into the widget area.\n2. All outputs go into the output area.\n3. All widgets in a cell direct their output to that one output area.\n4. clear_output only affects the output area.\n5. Deleting a cell removes the output and widgets.\n6. Re-running a cell should clear the output and widgets.\n7. Anytime a widget view is removed from the page, we need to clean up that view.\n8. When all views are gone from the page do we cleanup the widget itself? (I don't remember exactly how this works.).\n\nThe behavior I am observing is only a bug with 6 and possible 7/8. But I don't see a problem with the abstractions themselves. Can you clarify? There might be, but I am not seeing it.\n\nI know you want to have multiple output areas. But that is a new feature/abstraction that should be considered on its own. I am +1 on thinking more about adding that feature, but I don't see how it is related to the current bug or leaks in our current abstractions.\n"
  },
