    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "My abstraction was much simpler: the input cells have output below them, and the output is either printed or display()ed.  Oh no! some of the output gets erased, but other output doesn't.  Oh yeah, the output actually has two types, so I have to think about whether display() is creating a widget, or some other kind of output.  It's confusing that display() can create two drastically different kinds of output with different lifecycles.\n\nBut I see your point too.  I think mine is simpler, but I understand not wanting to change things too much right before 2.0.\n"
  },
